所有谜题都有一个圆形起点和一个具有圆形末端线段的目标点，玩家需要寻找一条从起点到达终点的路径，路线不能交叉。这些谜题的目标是找到完成它们的正确道路，但并不总限于简单地完成迷宫。迷宫可能有几个起点和终点；玩家可能要找到合适的起点才能完成迷宫，或者弄清楚如何到达一个特定的终点来触发周围环境事件，如移动平台。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theverge.com/2014/6/13/5805392/the-witness-ps4-hands-on|title='The Witness' is the modern day 'Myst' you've been waiting for|accessdate=2016-02-22|date=2014-06-13|last=Webster|first=Andrew|publisher=Vox Media|website=[[The_Verge|The Verge]]|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160301114550/http://www.theverge.com/2014/6/13/5805392/the-witness-ps4-hands-on|archivedate=2016-03-01}}</ref>每种谜题都包含一种表示该迷宫机制的符号语言。例如，路径外有黑白点方格的谜题需要玩家在迷宫中找到一个路径，使它可以按颜色分隔这些方格。<ref name="kotaku e3 2013" />其他一些谜题则需要玩家利用周围环境来解决，如研究附近一棵模仿谜题的带有树枝的树，或观察附近与谜题布局一致的地板和墙壁<ref name="kotaku e3 2013" /><ref name="kotaku pax">{{cite web|url=http://kotaku.com/5631002/a-tantalizing-session-with-the-witness-the-next-game-from-the-creator-of-braid|title=A Tantalizing Session With The Witness, The Next Game From The Creator Of Braid|accessdate=2010-09-06|date=2010-09-06|last=Totilo|first=Stephen|publisher=Gawker Media|website=[[Kotaku|Kotaku]]|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100909041624/http://kotaku.com/5631002/a-tantalizing-session-with-the-witness-the-next-game-from-the-creator-of-braid|archivedate=2010-09-09}}</ref><ref name="eurogamer preview">{{cite web|url=http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2011-08-24-the-witness-preview|title=The Witness - Preview|accessdate=2011-08-24|date=2011-08-24|last=Donlan|first=Christian|publisher=[[Gamer_Network|Gamer Network]]|website=[[Eurogamer|Eurogamer]]|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110829075248/http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2011-08-24-the-witness-preview|archivedate=2011-08-29}}</ref>。岛上每个区域的谜题机制是一致的，而且经常会带有玩家早期探索的区域出现的一系列谜题，这一设计旨在帮助玩家识别和理解谜题机理与符号的含义。后来的谜题会使用一致的符号语言将两种或更多机制结合到一起<ref name="arstech review">{{cite web|url=http://arstechnica.com/gaming/2016/01/the-witness-review-an-island-where-knowledge-mystery-are-the-treasures/|title=The Witness review: A haunting, beautiful, coldly logical puzzle allegory|accessdate=2016-01-27|date=2016-01-25|last=Machkovech|first=Sam|publisher=[[Condé_Nast|Condé Nast]]|website=[[Ars_Technica|Ars Technica]]|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160126130425/http://arstechnica.com/gaming/2016/01/the-witness-review-an-island-where-knowledge-mystery-are-the-treasures/|archivedate=2016-01-26}}</ref>。

大多数谜题散落在岛上可辨识的与视线齐平的面板上，往往与电线相连。一旦一个谜题被解开，电线会亮起并引导玩家到达下一个谜题。在一些谜题中这些面板也被纳入了游戏的架构，如有一种谜题玩家需要通过一个半透明的面板观察背景元素以确定解决方法。<ref name="kotaku pax" /><ref name="eurogamer preview" />有些不明显的谜题内建于环境本身，玩家需要找到正确的便于观察的位置来完成它<ref name="arstech review" />。玩家可在任意时刻进入迷宫绘制模式，此时屏幕会以白色边框标示。在这种模式下，玩家不能移动，以便使用他们的控制器画出眼前迷宫的路径。该模式会在玩家解开谜题或手动取消后结束。通常情况下，这种模式在面板前被啟動，直接将玩家视角转移至面板，但它也可以在其他任意时间被啟動以解决那些基于有利位置的的谜题。<ref name="arstech review" />无论谜题正确解开与否，几乎所有的谜题都会通过声音或视觉效果提供即时反馈<ref name="arstech review" />。

游戏为开放世界，岛上特定区域的谜题也以非线性形式呈现。玩家可能会遇到一些带有他们还没有学会的符号语言的谜题。这种情况下，玩家不需要在一个谜题上较劲儿，可以去其他地区走走并解开那里的解谜，或许玩家会对新的符号语言有了深入了解或者对难题的解决有了灵感。<ref name="wired sept2015" />布洛指出游戏还有比迷宫更重要的东西，“关键在于当玩家理解了迷宫表达的微妙的东西时，他们的脑海会中涌现出如魔法一般的感觉——因为这些迷宫不只是谜题，它们凝聚了交流的线条，使自身变得更加复杂并最终说出了令人惊讶的东西”<ref name="eurogamer mazes">{{cite web|url=http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2010-10-22-jonathan-blow-asks-fans-to-have-faith|title=Jonathan Blow asks fans to "have faith"|accessdate=2010-10-22|date=2010-10-22|last=Bramwell|first=Tom|publisher=[[Gamer_Network|Gamer Network]]|website=[[Eurogamer|Eurogamer]]|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101025111726/http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2010-10-22-jonathan-blow-asks-fans-to-have-faith|archivedate=2010-10-25}}</ref>。

录音遍布了整个岛屿，内有一些深刻的名人名言，这些名人有[[释迦牟尼|释迦牟尼]]、[[伯尔赫斯·弗雷德里克·斯金纳|伯尔赫斯·弗雷德里克·斯金纳]]和[[威廉·金頓·克利福德|威廉·金顿·克利福德]]等<ref name="kotaku e3 2013" /><ref name="eurogamer preview" /><ref name="slant review">{{cite web | url = http://www.slantmagazine.com/games/review/the-witness | title = The Witness - Game Review | first = Aaron | last = Riccio | website = Slant | date = 2016-02-01 | accessdate = 2016-02-01 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160211064730/http://www.slantmagazine.com/games/review/the-witness | archivedate = 2016-02-11 }}</ref><ref name="gamesradar meaning">{{cite web | url = http://www.gamesradar.com/eureka-moment-what-witness-story-really-about/ | title = That 'Eureka' moment: what The Witness is really about | first = David | last = Roberts | website = [[GamesRadar|GamesRadar]] | publisher = [[Future_US|Future US]] | date = 2016-02-03 | accessdate = 2016-02-04 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160205094532/http://www.gamesradar.com/eureka-moment-what-witness-story-really-about/ | archivedate = 2016-02-05 }}</ref>。为这些名言配音的演员有{{Le|阿什丽·约翰逊|Ashley Johnson}}、{{Le|菲尔·拉马|Phil LaMarr}}、马修·沃特森（{{Lang|en|Matthew Waterson}}）和泰拉·德瓦（{{Lang|en|Terra Deva}}）<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.vg247.com/2016/01/14/the-witness-ps4-screenshots-voice-cast/ | title = The Witness cast includes Phil LaMarr and Ashley Johnson, new screenshots released | first = Stephany | last = Nunneley | date = 2016-01-14 | accessdate = 2016-01-14 | website = [[VG247|VG247]] | publisher = [[Videogaming247|Videogaming247]] | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160115225419/http://www.vg247.com/2016/01/14/the-witness-ps4-screenshots-voice-cast/ | archivedate = 2016-01-15 }}</ref>。玩家还能遇到一个剧场，那里可以播放一些短片，如[[詹姆斯·伯克_(科学史家)|詹姆斯·伯克]]的电视剧《{{Le|Connections (电视剧)|Connections (TV series)|Connections}}》和[[安德烈·塔尔科夫斯基|安德烈·塔尔科夫斯基]]执导电影《[[鄉愁_(電影)|乡愁]]》的结局<ref name="gamesradar meaning" /><ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.pastemagazine.com/articles/201